assessment_details.task_description:
Word limit: 2500 words (excluding attachments)

You are required to:

select ONE (1) of the three topics assigned for this assessment item

identify a suitable research problem or gap in knowledge

develop a considered research proposal to address this research problem or gap in knowledge.

The research proposal should include the following:

brief background to the research problem and how it aligns with previous studies and literature;

project aims, research questions, objectives and/or hypotheses;

significance or importance of the proposed research academically or for practice/policy (the so what question!);

research philosophy, design, sampling and proposed data collection methods;

potential research validity and reliability issues as well as limitations;

proposed data analysis techniques to be employed and how the data may be presented;

research timeline and budget;

reference list.

It is expected that the report will integrate and use key concepts and material from the course to support and justify the details outlined in the proposal. In particular, the proposal will need to integrate and use research method texts/articles in the report to justfy decisions. It is critical that effort be made to ensure a clear link is made between the research design, implementation and analysis.

The proposal should be written in a structured format and follow the sub headings as outlined above. The proposal itself should be detailed enough for a researcher to successfully implement the proposal and collect data.

Further information on the assessment task will be provided in class.
